                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13558305" author="stack" created="Sun, 20 Jan 2013 16:29:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wonder if we are pulling fat rows if we shouldn&apos;t log it in regionserver logs... say, if the size is &amp;gt; 1MB/10MB... log detail on it (same as when slow query but that needs detail...)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13558319" author="stack" created="Sun, 20 Jan 2013 17:17:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Add region to these messages in the UI &apos;Fri Oct 26 01:24:52 UTC 2012 	IPC Server handler 49 on 10304 	RUNNING (since 0sec ago) 	Servicing call from 10.4.19.33:38422: multi (since 0sec ago)&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13559917" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 22 Jan 2013 19:30:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Things like slow query log should have region encoded name and some row key. And +1 on printing when we are returning a big response, with details.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14269086" author="clehene" created="Thu, 8 Jan 2015 09:39:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking as improvement &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jdcryans&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jdcryans&quot;&gt;Jean-Daniel Cryans&lt;/a&gt; still want this? Would it be worth to add a more detailed description of the desired improvement? Maybe it would tempt someone...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14273783" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 12 Jan 2015 17:05:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=clehene&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;clehene&quot;&gt;Cosmin Lehene&lt;/a&gt; Things have changed a lot since then so I&apos;m not sure what kind of work is required now. I&apos;d close this unless someone is planning on working on it now that there&apos;s noise.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14273816" author="clehene" created="Mon, 12 Jan 2015 17:39:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jdcryans&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jdcryans&quot;&gt;Jean-Daniel Cryans&lt;/a&gt; I think the issue title should be &quot;per region read/write sizes in metrics&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
I think this is a legit feature not sure if it is already there or not or how hard it would be to add (perhaps not very hard). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14273903" author="stack" created="Mon, 12 Jan 2015 18:31:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have basic per-region metrics now. Resolving as &apos;not-a-problem&apos;.  Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=clehene&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;clehene&quot;&gt;Cosmin Lehene&lt;/a&gt; for the kick.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
